div.p:
To enable a localization of an organization or to specify names of places with identical
        names it is recommendable to use a controlled vocabulary for names of places and countries.
        In this case the following attributes are particularly relevant: 

@authority: to record the list from which a controlled value is taken, e.g. the
            Thesaurus of Geographic Names (TGN),

@authURI (authority URI): to record the web-accessible location of the controlled
            vocabulary from which the value is taken,

@dbkey (database key): to record a value which serves as a primary key in an
            external database.
